<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministers: Deportation of Kurds To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministers: Deportation of Kurds To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0605141494 Hamburg DPA in German 1338 GMT 6 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0605141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Heringsdorf (DPA) -- At their regular conference on 
Friday [6 May] the interior ministers of the laender were not 
able to agree to a stop to the deportations of Kurds. This was 
stated by Saxony's Interior Minister Heinz Eggert (Christian 
Democratic Union) in Heringsdorf on the Baltic Sea island of 
Usedom. A joint working group is now supposed to examine to 
what extent victims' descriptions of being tortured after their 
return to Turkey are correct. Eggert criticized the work of the 
Foreign Ministry, which "did not" examine these reports "quickly 
enough and did not eliminate all doubts." 
  At the beginning of the meeting, FRG Interior Minister 
Manfred Kanther (Christian Democratic Union) presented a report 
on the security situation. In addition, the agenda also 
included the observation of the right-wing extremist 
Republikaner, equal rights for policemen in eastern and western 
Germany, as well as cooperation with the police in East Europe. 

</TEXT>

