<H3> <TI>   Verheugen Calls For Alliances Against Republikaner </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Verheugen Calls For Alliances Against Republikaner </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0805172594 Hamburg DPA in German 1351 GMT 8 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0805172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guenter Verheugen, federal manager of the Social 
Democratic Party of Germany, has called upon his counterparts of 
the Christian Democratic Union, Christian Social Union, Free 
Democratic Party, and Alliance 90/Greens to form an alliance to 
act against the radical right-wing Republikaner. In a letter 
cited by the ZDF "Bonn Direkt" program on Sunday [8 May], 
Verheugen suggests that the democratic parties should hold 
counterdemonstrations against Republikaner election campaign 
rallies in communities, cities, and rural districts. According 
to Verheugen, people react helplessly time and again, by 
counterdemonstrations that often end up in violence and "provoke 
civil war-like scenes." 
  Meanwhile, Republikaner Chairman Franz Schoenhuber told a 
ZDF 
reporter why he is so often absent from committee meetings in 
the European Parliament. He said he does not want taxpayers to 
pay for the presence of a deputy who "cannot move anything 
anyway" in the committees. 

</TEXT>

