<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   G-10 Bank Governors Hold Talks on Forex Rates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    G-10 Bank Governors Hold Talks on Forex Rates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0905161894 Paris AFP in English 1557 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0905161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Basel, Switzerland, May 9 (AFP) -- Group of Ten 
central bank governors held a "confidential" discussion Monday 
[9 May] on the situation on the foreign exchange markets, German 
Bundesbank President Hans Tietmeyer said here after the 
governors' regular monthly meeting. 
  The talks came in the wake of large-scale concerted 
intervention last week by central banks to prop up the slumping 
U.S. dollar. 
  "We talked about developments on the forex markets and their 
implications for monetary policy", said Tietmeyer, who chairs 
the G-10 governors' committee. "Our discussion was 
confidential." 
  He added that the committee had not discussed exchange rate 
targets at their meeting at the Basel headquarters of the Bank 
for International Settlements. 
  The governors also talked about the derivatives markets, the 
growth of which is causing them some worries. "We decided today 
to make a study, to be completed in April 1995, of all 
participants on this market," the Bundesbank chief said. 
  He also said the governors were a little more optimistic 
than 
previously about the world economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

