<H3> <TI>   Bulgaria To Receive Energy Consumption Advice </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bulgaria To Receive Energy Consumption Advice </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0905122894 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 7 May 94 p 19 </F>
<F P=103> BR0905122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Netherlands Company for Energy and </F>
the Environment Helps Bulgaria Save Energy"] 
  [Text] Rotterdam -- The Netherlands Company for Energy and 
the Environment (NOVEM) is giving Bulgaria aid to reduce its 
energy consumption. This week, L. Petkanchin, the Bulgarian 
deputy minister for energy, visited NOVEM to hold further talks 
regarding a project for the local communities in his country to 
save energy. 
  Of the bilateral aid The Netherlands is giving to East 
Europe, NOVEM is paying for technical advice from consultants, 
modern measuring equipment, and supervision. Energy consumption 
by Bulgarian (Government) buildings, households, and industry is 
very high. There is the threat of an energy crisis because the 
bills can no longer be paid. One quarter of the fuel used for 
generating electricity is imported from Russia. 
  The Bulgarian partners in the project began by measuring the 
energy consumption of local communities. In addition, advice 
and training was given for improving organization and making 
cleaner use of heating and ventilation systems. 
  NOVEM's experience in energy saving in The Netherlands is a 
guideline. The Bulgarians were taught that they have to contend 
with not only a financial problem, but also a quality problem. 
According to NOVEM's T. Verkerk, Bulgaria can save 10 to 15 
percent of its energy consumption without any costs at all, and 
another 15 percent by making small investments. This project 
serves as an example and as a step toward wide scale energy 
saving projects to be funded by the Bulgarian Government, the 
East European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, and the 
World Bank. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

