<H3> <TI>   Turkish Cypriots Continue Negotiations in Vienna </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Cypriots Continue Negotiations in Vienna </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1005105894 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 10 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1005105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The negotiation process on the Cyprus problem will 
continue in Vienna. According to a statement issued by the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Defense, Foreign Ministry Under 
Secretary Ozer Koray and presidential adviser Ergun Olgun went 
to Vienna this morning to hold talks with Gustave Feissel, 
deputy special envoy of the UN secretary general, and with 
Robert Lamb, the U.S. special coordinator, in connection with 
the negotiation process. ANATOLIA reports that the talks will 
also be attended by Tugay Ulucevik, Turkish Foreign Ministry 
deputy under secretary and adds that Lamb is continuing to make 
efforts in connection with the confidence-building measures 
cited in the UN secretary general's report of 1 July 1993. 
Certain improvements in favor of the Turkish Cypriot side will 
reportedly be posited in Vienna. 

</TEXT>

