<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   FYROM Uses New Flag at International Sports Event </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FYROM Uses New Flag at International Sports Event </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705170394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1300 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0705170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM] team appeared at the 29th Karate Championship 
taking place in Birmingham, England, with a new flag. At the 
beginning, the Skopjeans told organizers that they had lost 
their flag. But a short while later they presented a new one. 
The new flag has a yellow sun with 42 rays and six lines 
connected together in the form of an X over a red background. 
The team paraded as The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia. 
The team captain later revealed that the new flag was given to 
them by his country's Sports Ministry. 
  ATHENS NEWS AGENCY reports that the fact that Skopjeans 
changed their flag indicates that they are ready to present an 
alternative solution and perhaps they are ready to abandon the 
Sun of Veryina which they had presented as their symbol. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

