<H3> <TI>   Narcotics, Terrorism Accord Signed With Jordan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics, Terrorism Accord Signed With Jordan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0705181994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0705181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkey and Jordan will cooperate in the struggle 
against narcotics smuggling and terrorism. An agreement was 
signed in Ankara today between Turkey and Jordan for the 
cooperation in the struggle against narcotics and barbiturates 
smuggling, international terrorism, and organized crime. During 
the signing ceremony, Interior Minister Nahit Mentese said that 
the cooperation envisaged in the agreement will contribute to 
the development of relations in other fields as well. 
  [Begin Mentese recording] This agreement will result in 
effective and comprehensive cooperation in the struggle against 
international narcotics smuggling, international terrorism, and 
other organized crime. It has also been decided to establish a 
joint committee to be comprised of the representatives of the 
two sides with the aim of supervising the implementation of this 
cooperation and eliminating its shortcomings. 
  Moreover, under the agreement, our countries will exchange 
experts as well as information and documents. [end recording] 
  In turn, Jordanian Interior Minister Salamah Hammad said 
that 
the agreement will further increase bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

