<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karayalcin Sees Cooperation Among Left Wing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karayalcin Sees Cooperation Among Left Wing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605163394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1530 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0605163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara-Sanliurfa, May 6 (A.A) -- Murat Karayalcin, 
Social Democratic Populist Party leader and deputy prime 
minister, said today that cooperation among left-wing parties 
for an election had a high chance of realization. 
  He was speaking to journalists on board a plane on his way 
to 
the southeastern city of Sanliurfa. 
  On the cancellation of three mayoral elections in Istanbul, 
of which two were won by the pro-Islamic Prosperity Party, 
Karayalcin said that this decision of the High Election Board 
created an opportunity. 
  He recalled that the board has thus far canceled results of 
15 mayoral elections. 
  `We shall spend efforts, by heeding the calls for the 
unification of social democrats, toward realizing cooperation in 
the left,' he said. 

</TEXT>

