  [Excerpt] Canada is cracking down on foreign ships fishing 
outside the 200 mile limit on the east coast. 
  The minister of fisheries, Brian Tobin, presented 
legislation 
in the House of Commons today to protect the Grand Banks. If 
passed by parliament the law would allow fisheries officers to 
board foreign ships, search them, and bring them back to a 
Canadian port to face charges. Fines could reach a million 
dollars. [passage omitted] 

