<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Press Blamed for `Distorted Image' Abroad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Blamed for `Distorted Image' Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1005143994 Rome LA REPUBBLICA in Italian 10 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> BR1005143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome LA REPUBBLICA </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "There Is No Fascist Danger"] </F>
  [Text] Rome -- Foreign concern at the presence of 
"neofascists" in the government "results from a distorted image 
which our country is conveying of itself abroad. The fear 
others have of us is our own fault." This is the opinion of 
CNEL [National Council for Economy and Labor] Chairman Giuseppe 
De Rita, who believes that "it is absurd to think that extremist 
movements of the [German] Republikaner type are making any 
headway in our country. Those who judge us from the outside 
have misinterpreted [National Alliance Secretary] Gianfranco 
Fini's attempts to constitutionalize the Right. The way that 
information has been presented in the Italian media has resulted 
in an element of distortion of reality. The picture that 
foreign countries have of Italy is precisely that which our 
national press and television networks have transmitted across 
the borders. It makes no sense," De Rita added, "to speak of a 
return of fascism, when only 1 percent of Italians profess to be 
fascists." Furthermore, in this period "we are witnessing an 
impoverishment of the middle stratum of the ruling class. There 
are increasingly fewer people who are prepared to take an 
interest in politics. The new government is having to `scratch 
about' more than the previous one. [Clean Hands Judge] Di Pietro 
himself has declined [Prime Minister-Designate] Berlusconi's 
invitation. Why should he have joined the Viminale's [Interior 
Ministry] bureaucracy considering that he enjoys much more 
autonomy conducting investigations, and that he is more popular 
than [Mayor] Giuliani in New York?" 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

