<H3> <TI>   * Armed Forces in Drive To Recruit More Women </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    * Armed Forces in Drive To Recruit More Women </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94EN0306C Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE in Danish 12 Mar 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> 94EN0306C </F>
<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE </F>
<F P=105>  Danish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Military To Recruit More Women"] </F>
  [Text] The military has begun a campaign to recruit more 
women. 
  "Equality was introduced into the three branches long ago, 
but presently women represent only 5 percent of military 
personnel. This includes 59 officers, 150 sergeants, and 750 
military police," said Lieutenant Colonel Jens Christian Lund, 
director of Military Service and Recruiting. He added that the 
military was hoping to increase that number. 
  The military's good experience with mixed-gender units was 
given as the reason for the campaign. "Women are not merely 
excellent soldiers and colleagues, they have brought a 
much-needed change in attitudes and standards to the formerly 
male-dominated milieu," said Lund. 

</TEXT>

