<H3> <TI>   UN Official Departs for Vienna Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Official Departs for Vienna Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1005172694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1005172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary general's 
alternate special representative in Cyprus, left this afternoon 
for Vienna. Tomorrow he will meet Turkish Deputy Foreign 
Minister Tugay Ulucevik and Robert Lamb, the U.S. State 
Department's special coordinator on the Cyprus issue. 
  Feissel noted in a statement that two Turkish Cypriots, 
advisers to Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas, will also be in 
Vienna. He added that during tomorrow's meeting the situation 
will be evaluated since the deadlock on the talks on 
implementing the confidence-building measures. The Vienna talks 
are expected to be the last before the UN secretary general's 
report is circulated by the end of next week. 
  Asked about the Lamb-Feissel-Ulucevik meeting, acting 
Government Spokesman Spiros Arotis referred to the statement by 
President Glavkos Kliridhis that the government does not expect 
anything from this meeting. 

</TEXT>

