<H3> <TI>   Change in FYROM Flag `Sign of Goodwill' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Change in FYROM Flag `Sign of Goodwill' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1005131994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1005131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our country considers the change in the Skopje [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, FYROM] flag to be a 
practical sign of goodwill. Government Spokesman Evangelos 
Venizelos also said that the government has received no official 
statement and that its information is limited to press reports. 
Venizelos repeated that the Greek Government wants a quick 
solution to the issue, but that this is a hope, a goal; it does 
not mean things are close to agreement. The only development in 
the issue of Skopje, Venizelos said, is the Thursday [12 May] 
meeting in New York between Ambassador Khristos Zakharakis, 
Foreign Ministry director general, and UN mediator Cyrus Vance. 
The Greek Government, Venizelos stressed, is not satisfied with 
the proposal for a mutual guarantee of borders. The spokesman 
concluded by saying that Skopje knows the conditions laid down 
by the Greek Government. They are international legal 
regulations that Skopje must respect. 

</TEXT>

