<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leader Visits Greeks in Albania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Leader Visits Greeks in Albania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0805191694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0805191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Democracy Chairman Miltiadhis Evert returned to 
Ioannina at noon today folloowing a two-day tour to North 
Epirus, during which he visited villages and towns where the 
Greek minority lives. In a news conference at Ioannina, Evert 
called on the Albanian leadership to respect the human rights of 
North Epirotes. Good relations with Greece, Evert said, are to 
Albania's benefit. He said that it is inconceivable for 
relations between the two countries to be at the level of 
serious misunderstandings on the eve of the 21st century. 
  Referring to Turkey's involvement in Greek-Albanian 
relations, Evert said that if something like this were to 
happen, Ankara would have chosen a wrong direction. Finally, 
Evert said that he will visit the Albanian capital only if the 
five Omonoia [organization of the Greek minority of Albania] 
officials of the Greek minority, currently in Tirana prisons, 
are freed. 

</TEXT>

