<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Urges Nationals To Leave Algeria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Urges Nationals To Leave Algeria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005191094 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Spanish Foreign Ministry has repeats its 
advice to Spaniards residing in Algeria asking them to leave the 
country. It also asks those who are planning to travel to 
Algeria to refrain from doing so because of the violence 
unleashed against foreigners. 
  A spokesperson for the Diplomatic Information Office said 
that after the last attacks on foreigners in Algeria, this 
ministry recommends that Spaniards residing in Algeria leave the 
country if their presence there is not essential. 
  The approximately 300 Spanish residents in Algeria, however, 
should contact the Spanish Embassy in Algiers if they have not 
done so yet. 
  The Diplomatic Information Office added that due to the 
repeated acts of violence against foreigners the advice 
recommending that people not travel to Algeria is still valid 
specially if they have no pressing reason for going there. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

