<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposes CSCE Observer Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposes CSCE Observer Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1105185694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1105185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has declared that 
terrorism cannot be judged on a human rights level and that 
Turkey categorically opposes the proposal to send a CSCE 
delegation to Turkey. Cetin replied to questions by Turkish 
reporters in Strasbourg, where he is attending the Council of 
Europe Committee of Ministers meeting. 
  Answering a question, Cetin warned that assessing the 
question of terrorism in Turkey from a human rights viewpoint 
creates the impression that terrorism is being supported. 
Sending a CSCE observer delegation to Turkey is definitely 
unacceptable, Cetin stressed. 
  In reply to a question on recent developments in northern 
Iraq, the foreign minister recalled that the region is part of 
Iraq and stated that it is out of the question for Turkey to 
mediate between clashing Kurdish groups. 

</TEXT>

