<DOCNO> FBIS4-65052 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu092cc_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-092 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Expects 1994 Economic Growth To Reach 1.6 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Expects 1994 Economic Growth To Reach 1.6 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1105112194 Paris AFP in English 1101 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1105112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, May 11 (AFP) -- Economic growth in the 
European Union [EU] should reach 1.6 percent this year, higher 
than the previously predicted figure of 1.25 percent, the 
European Commission said here Wednesday [11 May]. 
  The EU's executive, issuing its latest economic forecasts, 
added that growth measured by gross domestic product (GDP) could 
reach 2.5 percent in 1995, up from the previous official 
prediction of 2.1 percent. 
  Last year the EU's aggregate GDP shrank by 0.3 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

