<H3> <TI>   Italian Humanitarian Aid Convoy Departs For Tuzla </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Italian Humanitarian Aid Convoy Departs For Tuzla </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1005130294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1115 GMT 10 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1005130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Bosnia/Italy: Giant Humanitarian </F>
Convoy Sets Out for Tuzla"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 10 -- After a flurry of intense 
coordination efforts between Rome and Sarajevo, authorities the 
largest humanitarian convoy yet organized by the Italian 
Government, in cooperation with its Bosnian counterpart, set out 
today for Tuzla, an Italian Foreign Ministry communique 
announced here. 
  The convoy is made up of 35 local trucks with 17 belonging 
to 
the Italian Team, along with nine escort vehicles, and is 
carrying 450 [metric] tons of food (including 300 tons of rice) 
for the Bosnian city and environs. 
  The foodstuffs come from the warehouse in the Croatian city 
of Split where the Italian Solidarity Consortium and Italian 
cooperation officials have supplies stocked. 
  From the start of the year, Italian Cooperation has 
organized 
27 humanitarian convoys from the base in Split, distributing 
some 600 tons of food and other basic necessities to various 
localities in Bosnia, the Farnesina communique added. 
  Furthermore, another 16 tons of supplies were furnished to 
Bosnian refugees in Dalmatia over the same period, the ministry 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

