<H3> <TI>   German, Russain Officials Hold Talks in Bonn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German, Russain Officials Hold Talks in Bonn </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Bonn, Moscow To Install `Hot Line' </H4>

<F P=102> AU1005111194 Hamburg DPA in German 1028 GMT 10 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1005111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- A "hot line" will be installed 
between the Chancellor's Office in Bonn and the Kremlin in 
Moscow. News of this official agreement broke on Tuesday [10 
May], prior to the start of Russian President Boris Yeltsin's 
three-day visit on 11 May. According to the agenda for 
Yeltsin's visit, Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and Andrey 
Kozyrev, his Russian counterpart, will sign the agreement on the 
hot line between the two government headquarters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

