<H3> <TI>   48 Italians Arrive from Yemen 10 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    48 Italians Arrive from Yemen 10 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1005130094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1121 GMT 10 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1005130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Yemen: 48 Italians Evacuated as </F>
Conflict Deepens"] 
  [Excerpts] (ANSA) Rome, May 10 -- Forty-eight Italian 
citizens including 10 children who were evacuated from Yemen 
arrived at Rome's Ciampino airport this morning. They were 
airlifted via Djibouti aboard an Italian Air Force C-130. 
  Among them was the Italian Consul at Aden Maurizio Pavesi, 
who called the situation "relatively peaceful" but said that 
while all Italian nationals in South Yemen had been repatriated, 
those present in North Yemen had not yet been flown out. 
[passage omitted] 
  "The opposing factions are not attacking civilians and the 
fighting generally takes place at night," said Pavesi. "Our 
embassy at Sanaa will remain open so that the last Italians in 
the country will have a point of reference." [passage omitted] 
  Consul Pavesi said another military flight was expected to 
airlift out another 50 Italians tonight. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

