<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   France, Baltic States Sign Military Cooperation Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    France, Baltic States Sign Military Cooperation Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1105143994 Paris AFP in English 1427 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1105143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, May 11 (AFP) -- French Defence Minister 
Francois Leotard and his counterparts from the three Baltic 
states Wednesday [11 May] signed the first military cooperation 
accord among their countries in Paris. 
  Leotard said the agreements "open up new perspectives in 
relations between France and each of the three (Baltic) states" 
allowing bilateral exercises as well as joint manoeuvres within 
the framework of the NATO Partnership for Peace, a military 
coooperation agreement recently signed by several East European 
states. 
  Estonian Defence Minister Indrek Kannik stressed that his 
country and Latvia and Lithuania attached great importance to 
participation in all international forums. 
  Leotard said Wednesday's accords would provide for young 
soldiers to attend training courses in French military schools 
and for wide-ranging exchanges of military personnel. 

</TEXT>

