<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reiterates Decision Not To Resign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reiterates Decision Not To Resign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105155494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1436 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1105155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, 11 May (EFE) -- Spanish Prime Minister 
Felipe Gonzalez reiterated today, Wednesday, his decision not to 
resign and to remain in charge of the executive branch to 
achieve "an atmosphere of confidence, which is necessary for 
strengthening the economy." 
  In an appearance before the Parliament, Gonzalez recognized 
the "social alarm" and the "political uncertainty experienced in 
the last few days" in Spain, but he pointed out that "a greater 
atmosphere of instability would be created" if I were to resign. 
  Gonzalez said he was willing to ask for the parliament's 
vote 
of confidence but only "at the necessary moment and that moment 
is not here yet." 

</TEXT>

