<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel To Vote for EU Enlargement 16 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel To Vote for EU Enlargement 16 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105132594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1255 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The German Cabinet today 
authorized Federal Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel to vote in 
favor of the enlargement of the European Union [EU] at a vote to 
be taken by the EU members in Brussels on 16 May. As expected, 
the Government decision was unanimous, Government Spokesman 
Dieter Vogel announced. The European Parliament has already 
voted in favor of the admission of Finland, Norway, Austria, and 
Sweden to the EU. 

</TEXT>

