<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Warns of Possible Withdrawal From Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Warns of Possible Withdrawal From Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205110894 Paris Radio France International in French 1000 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, who is in 
Washington, asked the United States to support the political 
settlement to the Bosnian conflict proposed by Paris. He also 
threatened to withdraw the 6,000 French peacekeeping forces from 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] if there is no prospect of a 
political settlement. 
  Speaking at John Hopkins University, Alain Juppe said the 
French plan envisions the gradual lifting of international 
sanctions against Serbia once a cease-fire has been concluded 
and territorial partition agreed on. 
  Alain Juppe told U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
there is no question of spending another winter in Bosnia. 
Christopher remained very cautious. He reaffirmed that the aim 
of the United States is to obtain a cease-fire and a renewal of 
the peace talks between the two sides. We cannot predict 
precisely what will come of it, he added. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

