<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Opposes Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Opposes Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1105113894 Paris LE FIGARO in French 11 May p 9 </F>
<F P=103> BR1105113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE FIGARO </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alain Juppe, the RPR [Rally for the Republic] 
secretary general, believes that "there is no such thing as a 
magic solution to the unemployment problem" and advocates 
"simple measures" adopted by parliament rather than through a 
referendum, as was proposed by Philippe Seguin. In his 
editorial in the RPR weekly NATION MAGAZINE, the foreign 
minister states that "it is up to the political authorities to 
define simple measures, but which would constitute a real change 
with regard to the attitudes of the social partners, and to have 
them voted by parliament." 

</TEXT>

